The failure is not in the test assertion. It occurs while creating the client:

```text
RuntimeException: No Bearer authentication configured!
```

Your generated `ApiClient.setBearerToken(...)` only works when the OpenAPI-generated client contains an authentication scheme of type `HttpBearerAuth`. This generated client apparently does not.

Use a default `Authorization` header instead.

## Update `PingClientConfiguration`

Replace:

```java
apiClient.setBearerToken(properties.bearerToken());
```

with:

```java
apiClient.addDefaultHeader(
        "Authorization",
        "Bearer " + bearerToken
);
```

Final version:

```java
@Configuration
@EnableConfigurationProperties(PingScimProperties.class)
public class PingClientConfiguration {

    @Bean
    public ApiClient pingApiClient(
            PingScimProperties properties
    ) {
        ApiClient apiClient = new ApiClient();
        apiClient.setBasePath(properties.baseUrl());

        String bearerToken = properties.bearerToken();

        if (bearerToken != null && !bearerToken.isBlank()) {
            apiClient.addDefaultHeader(
                    "Authorization",
                    "Bearer " + bearerToken
            );
        }

        return apiClient;
    }

    @Bean
    public PartnersBeAp74737ResourceTypeApi
            partnersBeAp74737ResourceTypeApi(
                    ApiClient pingApiClient
            ) {
        return new PartnersBeAp74737ResourceTypeApi(
                pingApiClient
        );
    }
}
```

This is appropriate when the server requires a bearer token but the generated OpenAPI specification did not declare bearer authentication correctly.

## Updated test

Do not call `getBearerToken()` or inspect an authentication object. Test that the configuration completes without throwing and that the base path is set:

```java
@Test
void shouldCreateApiClientWithBearerToken() {
    PingScimProperties properties = properties(
            "https://ping.example.com",
            "test-token"
    );

    ApiClient result =
            configuration.pingApiClient(properties);

    assertNotNull(result);
    assertEquals(
            "https://ping.example.com",
            result.getBasePath()
    );
}
```

