## Why this happened

The generated client was likely produced from an OpenAPI definition that does not contain something equivalent to:

```yaml
components:
  securitySchemes:
    bearerAuth:
      type: http
      scheme: bearer
```

Therefore, this fails:

```java
apiClient.setBearerToken(token);
```

because the generated client cannot find a registered bearer authentication handler.

Using:

```java
apiClient.addDefaultHeader(
    "Authorization",
    "Bearer " + token
);
```

will send the same HTTP header without relying on the generated authentication metadata. Do not log `apiClient`, the header map, or the token.
